.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt HYPERWEAVER-AGENT.YAML 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm hyperweaver-agent.yaml
.Nd configuration file for the Hyperweaver Agent
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
file is the configuration file for
.Xr hyperweaver-agent 8 .
It is written in YAML format.
.Pp
Locations:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
Desktop (tray) mode:
.Pa ~/.config/hyperweaver-agent/config.yaml
(created with commented defaults on first run)
.It
Headless service mode:
.Pa /etc/hyperweaver-agent/config.yaml
(installed by the package, passed via
.Fl -config )
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION SECTIONS
.Ss server
HTTP server configuration.
.Bl -tag -width "bind_address"
.It Cm bind_address
IP address to bind the web server to (default: "127.0.0.1"). Keep the
loopback address unless the agent must be reachable from other machines.
.It Cm port
TCP port number for the web server (default: 9420)
.El
.Ss ui
Web UI serving.
.Bl -tag -width "enabled"
.It Cm enabled
Boolean enabling the Hyperweaver UI at /ui/ (default: true). When disabled
the agent is API-only and the root path serves a small JSON info document.
.It Cm path
Optional directory to serve the UI from instead of the copy embedded in the
binary (default: empty = embedded)
.El
.Ss browser
Tray "Open" behavior (desktop mode only).
.Bl -tag -width "path"
.It Cm path
Optional full path to a browser executable (or .app bundle on macOS) used by
the tray Open action. Empty selects the operating system's default browser.
.El
.Ss logging
Logging configuration.
.Bl -tag -width "max_size_mb"
.It Cm level
Logging level: "error", "warn", "info", or "debug" (default: "info")
.It Cm console
Boolean enabling human-readable logging on standard error (default: true).
Under systemd this output is captured by the journal. The Windows GUI build
has no console; the log file is authoritative there.
.It Cm file
Log file path. Empty uses the default location
.Pa <config dir>/logs/agent.log ;
the packaged service sets
.Pa /var/log/hyperweaver-agent/agent.log .
.It Cm max_size_mb
Maximum log file size in megabytes before rotation (default: 20)
.It Cm max_backups
Number of rotated log files to keep (default: 5)
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width ".Pa /var/log/hyperweaver-agent/"
.It Pa /etc/hyperweaver-agent/config.yaml
Service-mode configuration
.It Pa ~/.config/hyperweaver-agent/config.yaml
Per-user configuration
.It Pa /var/log/hyperweaver-agent/
Service log directory
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
The packaged default:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
server:
  bind_address: 127.0.0.1
  port: 9420

ui:
  enabled: true
  path: ''

browser:
  path: ''

logging:
  level: info
  console: true
  file: /var/log/hyperweaver-agent/agent.log
  max_size_mb: 20
  max_backups: 5
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Configuration errors prevent the agent from starting and are reported on
standard error and in the journal:
.Pp
.Dl # journalctl -u hyperweaver-agent
.Pp
Common configuration issues:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
Invalid YAML syntax (indentation, special characters)
.It
Unknown configuration keys (the parser is strict and rejects typos)
.It
Port conflicts with other services
.It
Log directory not writable by the service user
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr hyperweaver-agent 8 ,
.Xr systemctl 1 ,
.Xr journalctl 1
.Sh STANDARDS
The configuration file uses YAML 1.2 format as defined by the YAML
specification.
.Sh SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
Keep restrictive filesystem permissions on the configuration directory; it
will hold credentials in future releases. Leave
.Cm server.bind_address
on 127.0.0.1 unless remote access is required and understood.
